description:
&lt;p&gt;At the James Paget University Hospital NHS Foundation Trust we care for our patients, each other and ourselves. We want to be outstanding at what we do and ensure we do things open and honestly.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are seeking a highly experienced employment relations investigating officer to join the Trust’s Staff Bank, who can be called upon to undertake investigations on an ad-hoc basis.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The successful candidate will have substantial experience at manager level in an NHS setting and have significant experience of undertaking highly complex employee relations investigations end to end in a large/complex organisation, preferably with experience/knowledge of working with Maintaining High Professional Standards. They must be able to investigate and analyse highly complex/multifaceted incidents logically, have experience of writing detailed and robust investigation reports and experience of presenting at formal hearings and being cross examined. Knowledge of HR best practice and associated employment law is also essential.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you believe you meet our requirements, we would love to hear from you.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Sarah Gooch,Interim Head of Workforce Operations, contact number 01493 452919.or email sarah.gooch@jpaget.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
